text: The Landtag of the Principality Liechtenstein () is the unicameral parliament of Liechtenstein. It meets in the capital of Vaduz. The Landtag has 25 members, split by the electoral districts of Oberland and Unterland. Its primary duty is to write, debate and pass bills (proposed laws). ==References== Category:Politics of Liechtenstein Category:National legislatures Category:Unicameral legislatures
title: Landtag of Liechtenstein
